  "prompt": "What are the causes for receding gums?",
  "response": "Receding gums can be caused by several factors:\n\n1. Poor oral hygiene\n- Not brushing and flossing regularly\n- Buildup of plaque and tartar\n\n2. Aggressive tooth brushing\n- Using hard-bristled toothbrush\n- Brushing too forcefully\n\n3. Periodontal diseases\n- Gingivitis\n- Periodontitis\n- Bacterial infections\n\n4. Genetic predisposition\n- Some people are more susceptible to gum recession\n\n5. Hormonal changes\n- Puberty\n- Pregnancy\n- Menopause\n\n6. Tobacco use\n- Smoking\n- Chewing tobacco\n\n7. Teeth grinding (bruxism)\n- Puts excessive pressure on gums\n\n8. Misaligned teeth\n- Uneven bite\n- Crooked teeth\n\n9. Medical conditions\n- Diabetes\n- HIV\n- Autoimmune disorders\n\n10. Age\n- Natural gum tissue deterioration\n- Decreased collagen production\n\n11. Lip or tongue piercings\n- Can cause gum irritation and recession\n\nPrevention involves good oral hygiene, regular dental check-ups, and addressing underlying health issues.",
